				Eh,
<br />

<br />
It is just that I see many anti-American stuff going around and...
<br />

<br />
Well, most of the time the peoples doing it dislike Bush and the American Leadership.  Okay, you hate them, well, not that I approve of this hating, but if you must hate them you NEED to remember that more then 99% of the Americans have NOTHING to do with them.
<br />

<br />
Oh, they vote for them?  Do they really have much of a great choice there?  Even an American that support their leaders have usually little in common with say leaders.
<br />

<br />
Hating the Americans based on a few leaders is VERY SHORT SIGHTED!
<br />

<br />
I humbly think that Americans, are after Quebecers(eh, self estime) the nicest folks around with Canadians, the Frenchs and the Britishs!  
<br />

<br />
If you must hate someone, go ahead, hate Bush, he is responsible and at any rated been paid for that, but do not hate all the Americans for that.  I dont see an American hating all Iraqis peoples, they hate Hussein and the terrorists leaders...and very rarely(and wrongly) some highly religious folks.  They dont even hate a terrorist that is dumbly following his leader, they will stop him of course, but they do not hate him.<br />
