Through my flippancy the point is that, yes the USA has assisted in many areas.  The world owes great thanks to the USA for many things.  But let's not pretend that they do it for other than selfish reasons, have not done a great deal of real damage to the world, or have have never turned their back on a nation (in fact interfered with other countries trying to help) facing hundreds of thousands of deaths.  The USA has helped, they have also destroyed, it all depends on wether or not there is something in it for them.  In some cases the USA has let hundreds of thousands die because there is nothing in it for them.  In others the USA has killed thousands simply to support business interests.  If I help a little old lady cross the street that is noble.  However, it does not excuse me for killing the little old lady on the next block for her pocket change.
<br />

<br />
If a nation wants to operate like this fine.  But let's not pretend it is otherwise and expect great cudos for behavior that is motivated by selfishness, greed, and arrogance. We'll thank you for your help.  We will not forgive previous or future atrocities.  We will not praise your motivations.  We understand them too well.<br />
